O friends! no friends, to King, Church and state. Or, Thames, Twede and Tyne paraell'd [sic] with Romes Tyber and king-poysoning Po. With positions and practices from Rome and from Rhemes, from Edenburgh and Geneva, poiz'd to some purpose, as the case now stands : and, presented to all impartiall patriots and Presbyterians. / By Veridicus, præterea nihil. Veridicus.
[2], 21, [1] p.
Printed by R. Austin, London : 1648.
Annotation on Thomason copy: "March 20th"; the 8 in imprint date is crossed out and replaced with "7". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
